laims are binding on us. She then extends this interpretation into two vexed areas of Levinas scholarship: the possibility of developing an environmental ethics based on his work and the possibility of applying his ethics to the emancipatory projects of new left social movements.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aPhilosophy -- Ethics and Moral Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy -- Poststructuralism and Phenomenology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080477978440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804779784423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804779784/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles